XVI. TO GROSPHUS

Otium divos rogat z'n patenti

EST! prays the mariner, by storm Caught in the wide AEgaean sea — When blaekening clouds the skies deform And lone stass glimmer fitfully.

For rest the furious Thracians cry, The quivered Parthians pray for rest 3 Rest‚ Grosphus, neither gold can buy Nor precious stones nor purple vest.

In vain your treasures you display Or lictor⁷s summonses to quit — The cares and tumults still will stay

That round the gilded eeilings flit. 101
